definition.value: A member of the class of methylindoles that is 1H-indole substituted by (2S)-butan-2-yl, methyl, N-[(4,6-dimethyl-2-oxo-1,2-dihydropyridin-3-yl)methyl]acetamide, and 6-(piperazin-1-yl)pyridin-3-yl groups at positions 1, 3, 4, and 6, respectively. It is a potent and highly selective inhibitor of EZH2 methyltransferase (IC50 = 9.9 nM).
A glycine derivative that is glycine in which one of the hydrogens of the amino group is substituted by a 2-methoxy-5-({[2-(2,4,6-trimethoxyphenyl)ethenyl]sulfonyl}methyl)phenyl group.
